rough culture and ethnicity to learn more about the history of the area. Kapamodz and Zanibou are the district's significant and alluring hills, and Tizu, Lanye, and Sedzu are their principal rivers. The Phek waterfall orchid vibes are the cherry on top of this unusual tourist destination. This out-of-the-way location in Nagaland is a riot of colour and celebration, which might enhance the visitor's pleasure. On a trip to Phek, tourists can partake in hobbies like birdwatching, hiking, and trekking because the less travelled area will give visitors something to think about. 10. Intanki Wildlife Sanctuary The Intanki National Park, one of Nagaland's most well-liked tourist destinations, spans a total area of 202.02 kilometres square. In 1993, it was designated as a national park. The enormous tract of equatorial forest is renowned for its picturesque scenery and semi-tropical flora. The government designated the park as an elephant reserve in the year 2005. The Intanki Wildlife Sanctuary in Nagaland provides thrills for those who enjoy wildlife and the outdoors. The wildlife reserve is home to unique creatures, including sloth bears, wild dogs, flying squirrels, barking deer, and black storks, among others. Dense vegetation and semi-tropical trees fill the region. One can take part in exciting pursuits while visiting Nagaland's lush wonderland, such as camping, trekking, mountain climbing, and hiking. The park is frequented by hikers and outdoor enthusiasts and has beautiful valleys, mountains, and camping areas. Animal lovers can also enjoy the natural splendour of the park because of its stunning topography. One can observe much wildlife, including pheasants, kingfishers, kaleej, black storks, and white-breasted hornbills. Shilloi Lake, Japfu Peak, and Pulie Badze are a few of the additional locations nearby the national park that are worth seeing. This Nagaland tourist destination is easily accessible from the airport and train station in Dimapur because of the frequent government and private buses that run between Kohima and Dimapur. From Kohima, one can also take a taxi to the national park. The airport in Dimapur is conveniently connected to several of India's largest cities, including Kolkata, Guwahati, Bengaluru, and Delhi. Furthermore, the railway station has connections to both Kolkata and Guwahati. The period of November through February are the ideal times to travel to this region in the North East. To make the most of one's holiday, they can also make arrangements with the woodland rest house. The circuit house and the PWD Inspection Bungalow are a couple of the other lodgings. Next TopicTourist Places in Pushkar ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions Trending Technologies Artificial Intelligence AWS Selenium Cloud Computing Hadoop ReactJS Data Science Angular 7 Blockchain Git Machine Learning DevOps B.Tech / MCA DBMS Data Structures DAA Operating System Computer Network Compiler Design Computer Organization Discrete Mathematics Ethical Hacking Computer Graphics Software Engineering Web Technology Cyber Security Automata C Programming C++ Java .Net Python Programs Control System Data Mining Data Warehouse Javatpoint Services JavaTpoint offers too many high quality services. Mail us on [email protected], to get more information about given services. Website Designing Website Development Java Development PHP Development WordPress Graphic Designing Logo Digital Marketing On Page and Off Page SEO PPC Content Development Corporate Training Classroom and Online Training Data Entry Training For College Campus JavaTpoint offers college campus training on Core J