nd semi-tropical trees fill the region. One can take part in exciting pursuits while visiting Nagaland's lush wonderland, such as camping, trekking, mountain climbing, and hiking. The park is frequented by hikers and outdoor enthusiasts and has beautiful valleys, mountains, and camping areas. Animal lovers can also enjoy the natural splendour of the park because of its stunning topography. One can observe much wildlife, including pheasants, kingfishers, kaleej, black storks, and white-breasted hornbills. Shilloi Lake, Japfu Peak, and Pulie Badze are a few of the additional locations nearby the national park that are worth seeing. This Nagaland tourist destination is easily accessible from the airport and train station in Dimapur because of the frequent government and private buses that run between Kohima and Dimapur. From Kohima, one can also take a taxi to the national park. The airport in Dimapur is conveniently connected to several of India's largest cities, including Kolkata, Guwahati, Bengaluru, and Delhi. Furthermore, the railway station has connections to both Kolkata and Guwahati. The period of November through February are the ideal times to travel to this region in the North East. To make the most of one's holiday, they can also make arrangements with the woodland rest house. The circuit house and the PWD Inspection Bungalow are a couple of the other lodgings. Next TopicTourist Places in Pushkar ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions Trending Technologies Artificial Intelligence AWS Selenium Cloud Computing Hadoop ReactJS Data Science Angular 7 Blockchain Git Machine Learning DevOps B.Tech / MC