rous plants overflowing with colourful blooms, fresh and luscious fruits, and freely flowing rivers will allure guests with their loveliness. Additionally, you may purchase deliciously fresh fruit. The tribe known as the Lotha lives in this area. An important destination in the Wokha region is a touristic village near Riphyim, which is well-known for its breathtaking views of a dam on the Donyan River. With a summit elevation of 1969 metres, Mountain Tiyi in the Wokha region is another well-liked tourist destination for the mesmerising scenery of Nagaland. Also, don't pass up the opportunity to observe the River Doyang from the mountaintop in a way that has never been seen before. The Nagas consider Mount Tiyi to be a sacred site because they think it is where the spirits of the dead reside. We may soothe our adventurous character by hiking to the impressive Mount Tiyi, which provides us with lush surroundings the entire way. As we hike up the mountain, we will learn more about the legends that are connected to it with the help of their famous folklore sung by them. Do not worry about getting there because the closest airport and train station are in Dimapur, from which we can take a taxi or a bus to Wokha. 6. Khonoma Green Village Khonoma Green Village, one of Nagaland's most undisturbed landscapes, is the product of consistent ethical living. This valley is a beautiful vacation location and a well-liked tourist attraction in Nagaland because of the tranquil scenery, clean air, and tranquil setting. Each home we will see here has been completely handmade using only crude ingredients that have been recycled or come from the earth. It is a place where the Angami community lives off of farming, spinning, and handlooms to provide for their daily needs. This place has flourished and is now a model and fantastic illustration of sustainable development for future generations. The Damant Tomb, Naga Historical Village, and Dovipie Guesthouse are some of the greatest tourist