ions in Nagaland, draws visitors with its mesmerising beauty in the shape of an unreal setting. Phek is a mountainous region with a diverse ecosystem. Shilloi Lake, in addition to the spellbinding hills, is a popular destination. Phek, which is filled with lakes, rivers, and other bodies of water, is the perfect place to find peace and quiet in the midst of nature. Another noteworthy site in this area is the tourist village of Khezhakeno. Khezakeno, a traditional hamlet located in the neighbourhood, can be explored for a voyage through culture and ethnicity to learn more about the history of the area. Kapamodz and Zanibou are the district's significant and alluring hills, and Tizu, Lanye, and Sedzu are their principal rivers. The Phek waterfall orchid vibes are the cherry on top of this unusual tourist destination. This out-of-the-way location in Nagaland is a riot of colour and celebration, which might enhance the visitor's pleasure. On a trip to Phek, tourists can partake in hobbies like birdwatching, hiking, and trekking because the less travelled area will give visitors something to think about. 10. Intanki Wildlife Sanctuary The Intanki National Park, one of Nagaland's most well-liked tourist destinations, spans a total area of 202.02 kilometres square. In 1993, it was designated as a national park. The enormous tract of equatorial forest is renowned for its picturesque scenery and semi-tropical flora. The government designated the park as an elephant reserve in the year 2005. The Intanki Wildlife Sanctuary in Nagaland provides thrills for those who enjoy wildlife and the outdoors. The wildlife reserve is home to unique creatures, including sloth bears, wild dogs, flying squirrels, barking deer, and black storks, among others. Dense vegetation and semi-tropical trees fill the region. One can take part in exciting pursuits while visiting Nagaland's lush wonderland, such as camping, trekking, mountain climbing, and hiking. The park is frequented by hikers and out